-- Costamagna Says He's Not Interested in UniCredit CEO Job, Corriere Reports
-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 2010-09-23T06:33:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/costamagna-says-he-s-not-interested-in-unicredit-ceo-job-corriere-reports.html
Claudio Costamagna, a former
investment banker at Goldman Sachs Group Inc., is not interested
in succeeding Alessandro Profumo as chief executive officer of
UniCredit SpA, the banker told Corriere della Sera in an
interview.  “The four deputy CEOs are perfectly capable to succeed
Profumo,” Costamagna said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net  